<html><head>
<title>CONSEQUENCES  Vol.2 No. 2 simberloff.html</title></head>
<body>



<b>Prof. Daniel Simberloff</b> is an ecologist who has served on the faculty 
of the 
Department of Biological Science at Florida State University in Tallahassee 
since 1968, with interests in conservation biology and the composition of 
biotic communities.  He is a member of the Board on Biology of the National 
Research Council, the Board of Governors of the Nature Conservancy, and 
the  Invasive Species Specialist Group of the International Union for 
Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources (IUCN).


<p>

</body>
