<HEAD>
<TITLE>Catherine S. Renault- CIT Managing Director for Technology Commercialization</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<!--BODY BGCOLOR=#E6E8FA-->
<BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrounds/rib-bk2.gif">

<CENTER>
<H2>Catherine S. Renault</H2>
<H3>Managing Director for Technology Commercialization</H3>
</CENTER>


<IMG ALIGN=left VSPACE=15 HSPACE=15 SRC="./images/csrenault.gif">
<P>
<P>
&#160;<BR>
&#160;<BR>
<HR>
<UL>
<B><LI>E-mail:</B> <A HREF="mailto:cathy@cit.org">cathy@cit.org</A>
<P>
<B><LI>Phone:</B> (703) 689-3000
<P>
<B><LI>FAX:</B> (703)  689-3041
<P>
<B><LI>Mail:</B> Suite 600, 2214 Rock Hill Road, Herndon, VA 20170-4200
</UL>
<P>
<HR>
<BR CLEAR=left>
<P>

<P>
Catherine S. Renault is the Managing Director for Technology Commercialization at the CIT.  She also is responsible for the Entrepreneurship Program.  Prior to joining CIT in 1993, Ms. Renault was the Director of the George Mason University Incubator Program, a business assistance center for start-up high technology companies.  
<P>
Ms. Renault's private sector experience includes five years as Director of Marketing for a division of Atlantic Research Corporation as well as various marketing and sales positions with AT&T and Data General Corporation.
<P>
Ms. Renault is Virginia's representative to the Science and Technology Council of the States of the National Governor's Association.  Ms. Renault currently serves on the Board of Directors of  the Century Club of George Mason University, Inc.
<P>
Ms. Renault is a native of Boston, MA.  She earned an undergraduate degree in government from Harvard University and an M.B.A. from the Darden School at the University of Virginia.
<P>

