<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>CIT's Partners & Intellectual Resources</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../backgrounds/rib-bk2.gif">
<CENTER>
<H1><IMG SRC="../../images/CIT.ribbon.trans.gif" BORDER=0>
 CIT Partners &amp; Intellectual Resources</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>

<B>
<P>
Within the Technology Industry Development unit of CIT, Technology 
Development Support consolidates all resources- both monetary and human- 
used to support the development of technology and the industry sectors
it serves.  Intellectual resources include public and private universities and colleges, 
federal and state laboratories and technology-based agencies, associations, 
etc.  Specifically, CIT works very closely with its Technology Development 
Centers (TDCs), the Technology Application Center (TAC), the Virginia 
Technical Information Center (VTIC), and CIT's Institutes, to assist high 
technology companies in the Commonwealth.
<P>
CIT's partners also include industry associations, regional technology
councils, state and regional economic development groups, regional
planning initiatives, the Virginia Technology Council, the Philpott
Center, state and federal laboratories and agencies, the Southern 
Technology Council, businesses and industry, etc.
<P>
</B>
<TABLE WIDTH=100%>
<TR>
<TD>
<LI><B><A HREF="./tdcs.html">Technology Development Centers</A></B>
