<HEAD>
<TITLE>CIT Industry Sector- Energy and Environmental</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../backgrounds/rib-bk2.gif">

<CENTER>
<H3><IMG SRC="../images/CIT.ribbon.tiny.trans.gif"> CIT Industry Sectors</H3>
<H1>Energy and Environmental</H1>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=0 HSPACE=8 SRC="./images/lakeview.gif">
</CENTER>
<P>

The Environmental Technology and Energy Program is focused on 
expanding sales and profits for Virginia's companies involved with 
environmental, energy, and sustainable technologies, products and 
processes.  CIT works with businesses in Virginia to aid in the 
identification and reduction of regulatory, stakeholder, institutional
and commercial barriers to the use of new technologies and processes 
developed by Virginia businesses and universities.  There is also an 
emphasis on working with Virginia businesses to access the high-growth 
foreign markets for environmental goods and services.

<P>
The CIT Energy and Environmental Industry Director is 
<A HREF="../people/dweiss.html">David Weiss</A>.  
For more information regarding this industry, please call him at 
(703) 689-3000 or send an e-mail to:  
<A HREF="mailto:david@cit.org">david@cit.org</A>.

<P>
For a list of Virginia companies in this industry sector, take a look
at the <A HREF="http://intercom.virginia.edu/cgi-bin/vtr-tech-query?Environmental+Technology+and+Energy"><B>Environmental Technology and Energy section</B></A> of the <A HREF="../VA.technology.html">Virginia Technology Resources (VTR)</A> list.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

&#160;<P>
Other potentially helpful links:<BR>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.bigyellow.com/">BigYellow</A> internet yellow pages
<LI><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Science/Energy/">Yahoo's Energy index</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Science/Engineering/Environmental_Engineering/">Yahoo's Environmental Engineering index</A>

</UL>

