<HEAD>
<TITLE>CIT Industry Sector- Electronics and Advanced Manufacturing</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../../backgrounds/rib-bk2.gif">

<CENTER>
<H3><IMG SRC="../images/CIT.ribbon.tiny.trans.gif"> CIT Industry Sectors</H3>
<H1>Electronics and Advanced Manufacturing</H1>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT VSPACE=0 HSPACE=8 SRC="./images/manufacture.gif">
</CENTER>

<P>
Virginia is home to 6,400 manufacturing and electronics companies 
located throughout the state, predominantly in the Western and 
Central regions.  The Electronics and Advanced Manufacturing Industry 
at CIT works to:
<UL>
<LI>Identify and create critical resources and programs essential to the industry;
<LI>Develop and implement industry-specific solutions;
<LI>Achieve focus programs and facilitate collaboration between services designed to assist existing manufacturing industries;
<LI>Promote selected emerging industries where Virginia can become a leader; and
<LI>Support initiatives that will create a climate for attracting industry into Virginia and encourage new company growth in manufacturing.
</UL>

<P>
For more information regarding this industry sector, please send an e-mail to 
<A HREF="mailto:wolfgang@cit.org">wolfgang@cit.org</A>.

<P>
For a list of Virginia companies in this industry sector, take a look
at the <A HREF="http://intercom.virginia.edu/cgi-bin/vtr-tech-query?Advanced+Manufacturing+and+Electronics"><B>Electronics and Advanced Manufacturing section</B></A> of the <A HREF="../VA.technology.html">Virginia Technology Resources (VTR)</A> list.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

&#160;<P>
Other potentially helpful links:<BR>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.bigyellow.com/">BigYellow</A> internet yellow pages
<LI><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Business_and_Economy/Companies/Electronics/">Yahoo's Electronics Companies index</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Business_and_Economy/Companies/Manufacturing/">Yahoo's Manufacturing Companies index</A>

</UL>

