<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Malaysian Delegation to Meet with Washington Area Businesses</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR=#E6E8FA>

<CENTER>
<HR>
<H1>Malaysian Delegation to Meet with Washington Area Businesses</H1>
<H3>Planning for Malaysia's new "Intelligent City", <A HREF="http://www2.jaring.my/msia/govt/putraj/put-main.html">Putrajaya</A></H3>
</CENTER>

On January 10 and January 14, Washington area businesses have the
opportunity to meet with a Malaysian delegation involved with the planning
and procurement for Malaysia's new, "intelligent" capital city, <A HREF="http://www2.jaring.my/msia/govt/putraj/put-main.html">Putrajaya</A>.
 This $8 billion project, scheduled for completion in 2005, will be the
world's first "intelligent city," propelled by the best in
telecommunications, transportation, and infrastructural amenities.  The
delegation's job is to identify the technology that will be used in the city
and to meet possible suppliers.  
<P>
The visit to the U.S. includes two briefing sessions and matchmaking
opportunities in Virginia: a plenary session on January 10 at
<A HREF="http://www.bah.com">Booz Allen Hamilton</A>
in McLean and a briefing/matchmaking session on January 14 at the
<A HREF="http://www.cit.org/facts/building.html">CIT Building</A> in
Herndon.  Please contact Nicole Miller of Booz Allen Hamilton
at (703) 917-2799/e-mail miller_nicole@bah.com or Nancy Vorona at (703)
689-3059/e-mail navorona@aol.com.  The
<A HREF="http://www.tda.gov">U.S. Trade and Development Agency (TDA)</A>
is sponsoring the delegation's visit to the U.S.
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A HREF="./news.html">[Return to CIT News page]</A>
<P>
 
</BODY>
</HTML>
