<HEAD>
<TITLE>Teleports and Economic Development- Virginia's opportunity for the approaching century</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#D8D8BF>
<P>
<B>Virginia's Center for Innovative Technology invites you to attend this free seminar:</B>
<CENTER>
<H1>Teleports and Economic Development</H1>
<H3>Virginia's opportunity for the approaching century</H3>
<P>
<B>January 14, 1997    9:30 AM - 12:00 PM</B>
<BR>Virginia's Center for Innovative Technology (CIT) - Auditorium
<BR>2214 Rock Hill Road, Herndon, Virginia 20170
<P>
<B>PLEASE REGISTER EARLY - Only 100 seats available.</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
In this age of teleports and intelligent cities, global wealth is 
accumulating to the world's major access nodes and great teleports. 
Virginia's coming access to ATM/SONET and an immense variety of optical 
fiber, terrestrial wireless, and satellite broadband infrastructure will 
enable Virginia companies and citizens to share in this wealth, as the core 
of global Internet in the Netplex and Potomac Knowledgeway transitions even 
now to Internet II. Join with the leaders of the global Teleport movement to 
learn how to adapt your company or institution... and how to avoid being left 
behind.
<P>
<CENTER>
<B>Speakers</B>
<P>
Dr. Robert D. Francis
<BR>Chairman of the Board - World Teleport Association
<BR><CITE>The Planet and Teleports</CITE>
<P>
Mr. Lou Zacharella
<BR>Executive Director - World Teleport Association 
<BR><CITE>Description and History of Teleports</CITE>
<P>
Mr. Stephen Tom
<BR>President & CEO - Washington International Teleport 
<BR><CITE>What IT Does and How It Works</CITE>
<P>
Mr. Danial K. Malone
<BR>Project Executive, CIT Telecommunications Projects
<BR><CITE>Teleports and Smart Cities: Challenges for Virginia s Economic Future</CITE>
<P>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>To register:</B>
<P>
By phone: call Jennifer Volk at (703) 689-3045;
<BR>By email: complete and submit <A HREF="jan97-register.html">online registration form</A>
<P>  
For more information contact Jennifer Volk at (703) 689-3045
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.cit.org/"><IMG BORDER=0 ALT="Virginia's Center for Innovative Technology" SRC="../images/cit-logo.thumb.trans.gif"></A>
</CENTER>
</BODY>
</HTML>
