<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Wolfgang Tolle- CIT Managing Director</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#E6E8FA>
<CENTER>
<H2>Wolfgang T&ouml;lle</H2>
<H3>Managing Director for Technology Industry Development</H3>
<H3>Industry Director - Information Technology & Telecommunications</H3>
<H3>Industry Director - Electronics & Advanced Manufacturing</H3>
</CENTER>


<IMG ALIGN=left VSPACE=15 HSPACE=15 SRC="./images/wtolle.gif">
<P>
<P>
&#160;<BR>
&#160;<BR>
<HR>
<UL>
<B><LI>E-mail:</B> <A HREF="mailto:wolfgang@cit.org">wolfgang@cit.org</A>
<P>
<B><LI>Phone:</B> (703) 689-3000
<P>
<B><LI>FAX:</B> (703)  689-3041
<P>
<B><LI>Mail:</B> Suite 600, 2214 Rock Hill Road, Herndon, VA 20170-4200
</UL>
<P>
<HR>
<BR CLEAR=left>
<P>
Mr. T&ouml;lle joined CIT in April 1993.  As the industry director for Information Technology and Telecommunications, Wolfgang T&ouml;lle is responsible for the entire IT&T business sector in the Commonwealth.  As Managing Director, Mr. T&ouml;lle oversees the management of all of CIT's technology and industry development programs.  Additionally, he is responsible for CIT's international programs and activities as well as strategic partnerships with regional technology councils, universities and many other organizations in Virginia.
<P>
Previously, Mr. T&ouml;lle was an Assistant Professor in the Department of Computer Science at the University of Dortmund in Germany where he concentrated on research, development and teaching operating systems, performance evaluation of computer systems, and programming languages.  During this time he held one of the first lectures in Germany on the programming language C++.
<P>
In 1989, he was project manager for software development and subsequently Deputy Director of Industry Projects at the software company Quantum in Germany.
<P>
In 1990, Mr. T&ouml;lle joined the German National Research Center for Computer Science (GMD) and became CEO of its office in Washington, DC.  In this capacity he led a team of 15 people and acted as liaison between the information technology industry, government and academia in the US and their respective counterparts in Germany.  Mr. T&ouml;lle is the author of several books on the programming language C++ as well as the Study and Research Guide in Computer Science.  He has also published several articles in German and American journals and frequently gives presentations on a variety of topics including the business and commercial aspects of the information highway, the future of IT&T in Virginia; and others.  As part of his current activities, he has served or currently serves:
<BR>
<UL><LI>as the Chairman of the Virginia Information Infrastructure Task Force
<LI>on the Information Technology Committee of the Governor's Opportunity Virginia Task Force
<LI>on the Virginia Technology Infrastructure '95 Task Force
<LI>on the Board of Virginia's Education and Research Network (VERnet)
<LI>on the Board Intelligent Transportation Systems Virginia (ITSVA)
<LI>on the Council of the Southeastern Virginia Network (SEVAnet)
<LI>on the Advisory Board of the Virginia-Scotland Partnership
<LI>on the Selection Committee for Bell Atlantic's 1996 Distance Learning Grants Program
<LI>on the Operations Committee of the 1997 Virginia Technology Summit
</UL>
<P>
Mr. T&ouml;lle received his masters degree in Computer Science and Business Management, summa cum laude, from the University of Dortmund, Germany in 1986.  He is a member of several professional organizations such as ACM, IEEE, the Internet Society and the German American Business Association.
<P>


</BODY>
